Map the submitted jurisdiction name to one of the canonical forms above. Accept common country-name variants, abbreviations, punctuation variants, and source-language variants when the intended country is clear.

Important scope choices:
- The allowed set is ASEAN-10 plus India, China, Australia, and the United States. No other country canonifies into this task.
- A subnational buyer, state, province, city, municipality, school, hospital, police unit, ministry, or public enterprise should canonify to the source-stated country jurisdiction when that country is in the allowed set.
- For multilateral procurement notices, canonify to the beneficiary, delivery, or project country stated by the source, not automatically to the agency headquarters country.
- A regional phrase such as "ASEAN" or "Asia-Pacific" is not itself a jurisdiction. Use a specific allowed country only when the source or submission makes one clear.
